overview: The user started by asking about multiple duplicate Vercel projects
  for their  app. I identified the issue, which was likely
  due to importing the same GitHub repository multiple times, and then, at the
  user's request, deleted the four duplicate projects using the Vercel CLI,
  leaving only the main  project. Following this, the user
  wanted to set up a development environment with a separate domain. I
  recommended creating a  branch and configuring Vercel's preview
  deployments with branch-specific environment variables. I created and pushed
  the  branch. We then reviewed the environment variables, and I
  corrected the  variable to ensure it was not
  active in production, redeploying production afterward. Finally, I provided
  the predictable Vercel URL for the  branch and, upon realizing it
  hadn't been deployed yet, triggered a deployment to make the development
  environment accessible.
